🛑 google this term: resource desert 

If you don’t have the time, I’ll explain it for you! ✨a summary is at the bottom✨

➡️ Resource Desert: An area that is experiencing a scarcity of important resources (grocery stores 🏪 pharmacies 🧑‍⚕️ healthcare ⛑️ parks 🏞️ clothing 👚) due to disinvestment. 

WHY IT MATTERS 👉🏾 Health 

Caused by 👉🏾 lack of fresh food 🍎 places to exercise 🏋🏼 mental outlets & doctors 🩻

🙋🏽‍♂️How do we inact change? 
1 word = real estate! 
Purchasing these properties & rehabbing them 👉🏾 increases property values of surrounding properties 👉🏾 provides economic opportunity through:

➡️ the real estate agents brokering the deal (👋🏽 that’s me 😂)
➡️the trades people renovating the property (contractors, electricians, & plumbers) 
➡️ future jobs from whatever the potential location becomes 

My goal 🥅 = follow the example set by Bethel Hardware in Bethel NC and invest in this properties in small town NC. 

🛑 SUMMARY 👉🏾 bring local businesses back to these small NC Main streets by reinvesting in these properties that have been left empty for far too long 
#bethelhardwarenc #supportlocal #supportsmallbusiness

Today I asked God to plant my feet on the path that they should go. ➡️ there is an anointing so great over my life  I’ve felt for some time👉🏾 I must remain humble & not lose sight of my purpose.

So confession I have done it in the past 🫢 a lot of real estate agents are told to do it. ESPECIALLY if you’re new. 

I knew when I was doing it I didn’t like it 🙈 but I was told that it was just a fear of rejection 😬 

WRONG 😑 

My gut was telling me this isn’t for me! 

I hate when people cold call me ☎️ I hate when they know everything about me (name, address, numbers, and emails) 😡 so knowing I don’t like it, why would I call people I don’t know with their name and addresses 👉🏾 all to get them to list their house 🏡

That’s why I make it a rule to 🚫never🚫 cold call 📞 and to run from any company who requires it 

My clients value my integrity 💕 that’s why they choose 🗣️ the doll of the NC 👉🏾 North Carolina Nicole w/ KW innovate

If you watch the news you’ve heard talk about Real Estate agent commissions. 

I LOVE what I do and I LOVE helping people💕 

🛑BUT there is almost always a huge misconception on what agents like me do and how we get paid. 

🙊No need to keep it secret I’m spilling the tea ☕️ 

The average FULL TIME REALTOR’s earnings last year was $31,900 @ 40+ hours a week. 

➡️As a REALTOR we do not get paid a hourly wage or salary and we only get paid if they sell a home and it closes. 

As an agent you could work with someone days, weeks, months, or years with no guarantee of a sale ever.🚫💵

Essentially We wake up each day unemployed going on Job Interviews and  deal with constant rejection. 

➡️➡️➡️They have lots of upfront expenses that must be paid out before they even get paid:

⭐️Broker Splits and Fees
⭐️Office rent and utilities
⭐️MLS Fees
⭐️NAR Fees
⭐️Local Association Fees
⭐️E&O Business Insurance
⭐️Extended Auto Insurance
⭐️Self-Employment Tax
⭐️State Licensing Fees
⭐️Advertising Fees
⭐️Showing Service Fees
⭐️Website Fees
⭐️Assistant's Salaries
⭐️Showing partners
⭐️Transaction coordinator
⭐️Yard Signs
⭐️Photographers
⭐️Videographers
⭐️Office Supplies
⭐️Business Cards
⭐️Property Flyers
⭐️Electronic Lockboxes
⭐️Continued RE Education
⭐️Legal Fees
⭐️Gas
⭐️Income taxes are not taken out so they have to put that aside around 25-30%.

👉🏾Don’t forget health insurance

Confession…😮‍💨

I use filters sometimes. I don’t always look the best. Some days on the farm I look like the Scrat from Ice Age🐿️. Some days I’m super pageant ready👑. Some days my hair is perfect. Some days my makeup is a mess. some days my confidence is through the roof⬆️, and others not so much⬇️ 

What am I getting at? 
⬇️⬇️⬇️

Well listen, in a world where filters are on every app we have, it clear I’m not the only one using them. I’m human 

If I’ve been your idea of perfection👉🏾 I shouldn’t be, cause I ain’t perfect and nobody is

And if you’ve felt the pressure of insecurities (I hate…. Or I wish I…) or not feeling secure enough (you should love the skin your in people shaming you for not feeling that way) 👉🏾 here’s a truth most people won’t say. 

✨✨Being confident 100% of the time is unrealistic. There’s not a soul I feel on this planet that is happy with every single aspect of themselves 24/7 it ebbs and flows. ✨✨

Sometimes you’ll get unfiltered sometimes you’ll get a filter. You don’t have to be perfect. 

😂 Enjoy this side by side comparison because I’m not ashamed to admit that even I forget that I’m beautifully and wonderfully made.

Go Pick Cotton! 
.
.
The only cotton I pick is Black! 
Let’s talk about it. ⬇️

I was able to tour a 5 generation cotton farm that’s reclaiming the narrative of cotton. 

Trigger warning ⚠️ mentions of American Slavery ➡️ history is history whether it’s good or bad! ⛔️

Due to American Slavery, Cotton Carrie’s a negative connotation especially in the black community. So how do we change that? 

The Tillery Farm (blackcotton.us) is 400 acres of black owned land, growing black owned cotton, being operated by a black family! 

Truly the manifestation of the ancestors dreams! 

Now, I’m not saying that there will ever be a time where cotton isn’t a sore spot but it is a key 🔑 part to our everyday lives (clothes, medical care, beauty) and our history. 

As Julius would say” cotton is our culture, let’s grow together”. 

I highly recommend checking out their episode of the PBS docuseries for more in depth dive into the history and impact of BlackCotton.US

Shop➡️ @blackcotton.us

Enjoy these shots 📸 of me picking oppression free cotton.

Wait til the good part…

When this home was purchased I was bright eyed and bushy tailed! I was so hopeful for what I knew it would become….

The task was daunting. Worn carpets & builder beige surrounded me. But as us realtors say this house had good bones. I saw that potential. 

Through dedication, tears, some coats of paint, and a couple thousand in some unexpected repairs (ouch to my pockets) 

This home was listed. But we weren’t in the clear. 

Just under 30 days we waited. Hosting open houses… we invited the neighbors…showing after showing… to find the right buyers. 

Those buyers were found and we are under contract!!! 

A home is more than the # of bedrooms & bathrooms. A home is more than square footage. It’s a story. 

And it all starts with a buyer, that becomes a seller to another buyer. And the cycle continues. 

Could that be you in 2024?

1 year in < 90 seconds 

& it still wasn’t enough to show how good 2023 has been to me ➡️ praying for what 2024 has in store for me!

Let me change you mind about older houses 🏡 
.
.
First off, 1960s houses often have a unique charm and character that you won’t find in newer homes. They have that retro vibe that can make you feel like you’re stepping back in time. 🕺💃

Another cool thing about 1960s houses is that they were built with quality materials and craftsmanship. They were made to last, so you can have confidence in the durability of the structure. 💪

And let’s not forget about the potential for customization! With a 1960s house, you can put your own personal touch on it and make it truly yours. Whether it’s updating the kitchen or adding some funky retro decor, the possibilities are endless! 🎨🔨

So, if you’re looking for a home with character, quality, and the opportunity to make it your own, a 1960s house might just be the perfect fit for you! 😉🏠

You must be new here… 
.
.
Considering we just hit 100k on instagram there’s a good chance you’re new so allow me to fill you in. 

Hey 👋🏽 I’m Nicole, I’m a sheltered small town girl from Rob Co with Big Dreams and wanting to make an even bigger impact. I put a crown 👑 on Agriculture as the National Mrs United States Agriculture 2023 and I help folk plow through real estate in my career as a realtor
